question: What are genes related to Type diabetes mellitus?
goldstandard: HNF1B, IL6, GPD2, HMGA1, IRS1, NEUROD1, IL6
agent_answer:

1. [HNF1B](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/HGNC:11630)
2. [AKT2](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/HGNC:392)

11. [SLC30A8](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/HGNC:20303)
12. [RETN](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/HGNC:20389)
13. [IGF2BP2](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/HGNC:28867)
